{"TopicId":199812,"ForumId":21,"TopicTitle":"Need some advice on a 2-seater lander, No DLCs","CreatedByName":"Axel_22","CreatedById":209623,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-01-25T00:49:08Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Axel_22","CreatedById":209623,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-01-25T00:49:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know, I know, \u0022Just use the MK2 lander can, it\u0027s easy!\u0022 but I\u0027m looking for something in 1.25m parts or whatever the diameter is. Basically MK1 lander can size. you can comment your advice/pics\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"InfernoSD","CreatedById":208873,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-01-25T03:44:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe basic lander can really is quite good. Nothing wrong with using two of them. Or use one lander can and one pod, which is what I did for my\u00A0landers in the beginning.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-01-25T05:18:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223914266\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022199812\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221611535748\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022209623\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Axel_22\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Axel_22 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know, I know, \u0022Just use the MK2 lander can, it\u0027s easy!\u0022 but I\u0027m looking for something in 1.25m parts or whatever the diameter is. Basically MK1 lander can size. you can comment your advice/pics\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust stack them in this case. If you want a two person, I would recommend using this part:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022File:Mk1CrewCabin.png\u0022 data-ratio=\u002265.00\u0022 width=\u0022400\u0022 src=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/images/f/f8/Mk1CrewCabin.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nand maybe add this part for control, any other probe would work too.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022File:HECS2.png\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022100.00\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022 src=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/images/b/b2/HECS2.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nattack a heat shield and parachutes, then bang! You got a two seater in the 1.25 diameter.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-01-25T05:58:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is going to be a craft sharing thing, and so moved to the craft sharing subforum.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Axel_22","CreatedById":209623,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-01-25T19:19:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223914337\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022199812\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221611551885\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022196529\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The Doodling Astronaut\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 hours ago, The Doodling Astronaut said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust stack them in this case. If you want a two person, I would recommend using this part:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/images/f/f8/Mk1CrewCabin.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022File:Mk1CrewCabin.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002265.00\u0022 width=\u0022400\u0022 src=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/images/f/f8/Mk1CrewCabin.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nand maybe add this part for control, any other probe would work too.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/images/b/b2/HECS2.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022File:HECS2.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022100.00\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022 src=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/images/b/b2/HECS2.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nattack a heat shield and parachutes, then bang! You got a two seater in the 1.25 diameter.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for the advice, gonna go play ksp now\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}